bug.short_desc: Docs: Low-level tutorial for web developers

long_desc.thetext: This tutorial should be a step-by-step manual which explains qooxdoo to web developers. In some steps we will show how to implement a feature in qooxdoo and in traditional HTML+CSS side by side. The goal is to convince those people that not have to think about browser switches and CSS hacks is worth the effort to learn qooxdoo.
Added Thomas.

(In reply to comment #14) > Created attachment 881 [details] > bom_demo
Gabi, thanks. I looked at it, and talked to Andreas, and we decided not to include it currently. It duplicates too much of the BOM skeleton, which the user has to create anyway. The tutorial itself should suffice to modify the files manually to match the final result.
We also did not include any archive downloads for other tutorials, like the Twitter tutorial. Rather, they offer Gist downloads for individual files, and that might be the way to go for this tutorial as well. The .zip is not lost, as it is attached to the bug (but would need a bit of tweaking, e.g. 'clasic.js' -> 'classic.js'). What further bothers me is the fact that the files in the .zip don't seem to mirror the tutorial, in the sense that they are exactly what you get when you follow the tutorial steps, which I think would be necessary.
I reviewed the tutorial page, did some changes, and also inserted some (visible) comments when I couldn't quite figure out what was going on. Please look through the page and try to react on the comments as you see fit.
I think somebody else should go through the tutorial, follow its steps and try to come up with a running application. If you are done, Martin should dispatch that.
